# Typography Rules (Strict Usage)

- **Default UI:** `body` in `index.css` sets the UI stack (`IBM Plex Sans Arabic`, `IBM Plex Sans`). Components **inherit** this — do **not** add `font-ui` on controls, labels, avatars, etc.
- **Long Arabic content** (Azkar, Quran, Dua, long passages) must use **`font-content`** (`Noto Naskh Arabic`) on those regions only.
- Never mix the content font into generic UI chrome.

# Implementation Guidance

- Do not use a `font-ui` utility in TSX/CSS for normal components; rely on inheritance.
- Apply `font-content` only where the text role is long-form religious or reading content.
- Use RTL-aware layout/alignment as required by the UI reference.
